members.description: Unable to determine whether the UUID of the server is valid. The server hardware is reporting an invalid Product ID.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Use the remote console and boot the server into the RBSU (ROM-Based Setup Utility).  Ensure that the Serial Number and Product ID are set correctly using information found on the server.  Reboot the server, wait until the remote console messages indicate that the server is no longer in POST (Power-On Self Test), then refresh the server hardware {"name":"CZJ9260730, bay 6","uri":"/rest/server-hardware/E968F0A6-0F2D-4BC3-BC50-7CFF00ADA1A8"}.

members.description: The port map, virtual identifier, or server location information may not be up-to-date in the iLO.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: This does not affect the appliance, but it may prevent HPE Insight Control server provisioning or NIC configuration in the iLO UI from operating correctly.  If you are not using these applications, you may clear the alert.  Otherwise, try resetting the iLO and then refresh the server hardware.
